title: Hemisphere
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

A //hemisphere// is the intersection of $$S^2$$ with a half-space
$$
H=\{\,x\in\mathbb R^3\mid\langle x,n\rangle\ge 0\,\},\quad \|n\|=1.
$$
A hemisphere is bounded by a [[great circle|Great circle]]. One of its poles, $$n,$$ lies inside the hemisphere, the other, $$-n$$ outside.